</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Akhani, H. &amp; Edwards, G. &amp; Roalson, E. H." box="[152,444,1766,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" pagination="931 - 956" refId="ref2109" refString="Akhani, H., Edwards, G. &amp; Roalson, E. H. (2007) Diversification of the old world Salsoleae s. l. (Chenopodiaceae): molecular phylogenetic analysis of nuclear and chloroplast data sets and a revised classification. International Journal of Plant Sciences 168: 931 - 956. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1086 / 518263" type="journal article" year="2007">
Akhani 
<emphasis box="[249,302,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2007: 948
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pallas 1803: 30) Akhani &amp; E. H. Roalson" authorityName="Akhani &amp; E. H. Roalson" baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityPageNumber="30" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[466,1230,1766,1792]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Pyankovia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachiata">
<emphasis box="[466,716,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">Pyankovia brachiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pallas, P. S." box="[734,923,1766,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" refId="ref2728" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1803) Illustrationes plantarum imperfecte vel nondum cognitarum, cum centuria iconum. Academico Petropolitano, Leipzig, 129 pp." type="book" year="1803">Pallas 1803: 30</bibRefCitation>
) Akhani &amp; E.H. Roalson
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Akhani, H. &amp; Edwards, G. &amp; Roalson, E. H." pageId="1" pageNumber="21" pagination="931 - 956" refId="ref2109" refString="Akhani, H., Edwards, G. &amp; Roalson, E. H. (2007) Diversification of the old world Salsoleae s. l. (Chenopodiaceae): molecular phylogenetic analysis of nuclear and chloroplast data sets and a revised classification. International Journal of Plant Sciences 168: 931 - 956. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1086 / 518263" type="journal article" year="2007">
Akhani 
<emphasis box="[1376,1429,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2007: 949
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrenk ex Meyer" authorityName="Meyer" box="[360,858,1805,1831]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachycarpa">
<emphasis box="[360,620,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">Sophora pachycarpa</emphasis>
Schrenk ex Meyer
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fischer F. &amp; Meyer, C. A. von &amp; Ave-Lallemant, J." box="[912,1201,1805,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" refId="ref2342" refString="Fischer F., Meyer, C. A. von &amp; Ave-Lallemant, J. (1843) Index nonus Seminum, quae Hortus Botanicus Imperialis Petropolitanus pro Mutua Commutatione Offert. Accedunt Animadversiones Botanicae Nonnullae, St. Petersburg, 97 pp." type="book" year="1843">
Fischer 
<emphasis box="[1013,1068,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 1843: 89
</bibRefCitation>
). The habitat of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joharchi &amp; Pirani" authorityYear="2013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Acanthophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yasamin-nassehiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">A. yasamin-nassehiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is threatened by human activities (road constructions between Showqan and Jajarm). On the basis of the IUCN Red List categories and criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[798,940,1882,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" refId="ref2437" refString="IUCN (2010) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, version 8.1. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from http: // intranet. iucn. org / webfiles / doc / SSC / RedList / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed: 6 March 2010)." type="url" year="2010">IUCN 2010</bibRefCitation>
) this species is here evaluated as critically endangered [CR, B1ab(iii) + B2ab(iii)]. Another endangered endemic species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rechinger" authorityYear="1940" box="[1090,1272,1921,1946]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Diaphanoptera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="khorasanica">
<emphasis box="[1090,1272,1921,1946]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">D. khorasanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) grows in the same place of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joharchi &amp; Pirani" authorityYear="2013" box="[327,590,1960,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Acanthophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yasamin-nassehiae">
<emphasis box="[327,590,1960,1985]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">A. yasamin-nassehiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, a conservation planning for the threatened ecosystem and species is needed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[152,1437,151,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[200,442,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Taxonomical notes</emphasis>
:—The new species certainly belongs to sect. 
<emphasis box="[1044,1197,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Oligosperma</emphasis>
, showing however peculiar inflorescence and stem characteristics. Morphologically similar species are 
<taxonomicName authority="Lipsky" authorityName="Lipsky" authorityYear="1889" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Acanthophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevibracteatum">
<emphasis box="[1201,1437,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">A. brevibracteatum</emphasis>
Lipsky
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shishkin, B. K." box="[272,519,229,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" pagination="892 - 896" refId="ref2843" refString="Shishkin, B. K. (1936) Acanthophyllum C. A. Mey. In: Komarov, V. L. &amp; Shishkin., B. K. (eds.) Flora of USSR 6. Izdatel'stvo Akademii Nauk SSSR, Moskva &amp; Leningrad, pp. 781 - 802, 892 - 896." type="journal article" year="1936">Shishkin (1936: 790)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Shishkin (1936: 787" authorityName="Shishkin" authorityYear="1936" box="[576,968,229,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Acanthophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lilacinum">
<emphasis box="[576,720,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">A. lilacinum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shishkin, B. K." box="[727,968,229,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" pagination="892 - 896" refId="ref2843" refString="Shishkin, B. K. (1936) Acanthophyllum C. A. Mey. In: Komarov, V. L. &amp; Shishkin., B. K. (eds.) Flora of USSR 6. Izdatel'stvo Akademii Nauk SSSR, Moskva &amp; Leningrad, pp. 781 - 802, 892 - 896." type="journal article" year="1936">Shishkin (1936: 787</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 892). It is characterized by short bracts never exceeding the calyx, non-glandular hairs, and brownish stems which are densely branched from the middle. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lipsky" authorityYear="1889" box="[419,643,306,331]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Acanthophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevibracteatum">
<emphasis box="[419,643,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">A. brevibracteatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having dense simple to multicellular hairs, non-angled ribs of the calyx, and convex bracts with hyaline margin, while differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shishkin" authorityYear="1936" box="[913,1056,345,370]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Acanthophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lilacinum">
<emphasis box="[913,1056,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">A. lilacinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by short bracts with non-crisped hairs, and by short thickened leaves (
<tableCitation box="[585,674,384,410]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,232,151,172]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison of A. yasamin-nassehiae, A. lilacinum and A. brevibracteatum. The characters are based on" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5072101" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5072101" box="[152,1291,1929,1950]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5072101/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" startId="2.[152,245,1929,1950]" targetBox="[166,1425,506,1900]" targetPageId="2">
